les this easily TACTICAL DECISION MATRIX For Your Specific Situation: Your Profile Factor\tPoints to MKdirs\tPoints to Directorly SaaS Founder Experience\t✅ Understands business building\t⚠️ Might prefer shortcuts Digital Marketing Skills\t✅ Can drive traffic effectively\t⚠️ Platform may limit marketing Long-term Business Goals\t✅ Building valuable assets\t❌ Renting, not building Technical Comfort\t✅ Can handle basic setup\t✅ No technical skills needed Budget Optimization\t✅ One-time cost efficiency\t❌ Ongoing expense model Control Preferences\t✅ Full customization control\t❌ Platform limitations Score: MKdirs 5/6, Directorly 1/6 FINAL RECOMMENDATION: STICK WITH MKDIRS 🎯 Why the Analysis is Clear: You're Building a Business, Not Renting One MKdirs = Asset ownership Directorly = Service subscription Your Background Demands Control SaaS founders need customization capability Platform dependencies limit growth potential Economics Favor Ownership MKdirs: $79 → Unlimited potential Directorly: $300+/year → Limited returns Strategic Flexibility MKdirs: Build whatever you envision Directorly: Constrained by platform capabilities The Bottom Line: Directorly.app is a valid solution for non-technical users who want a hands-off directory service. But for a serious entrepreneur with your background, it's the equivalent of renting when you could own. Your women's health directory deserves: ✅ Professional, trustworthy branding (MKdirs) ✅ Healthcare-specific features (MKdirs) ✅ Long-term business value (MKdirs) ✅ Cost efficiency (MKdirs) ✅ Growth potential (MKdirs) Action Plan: Skip Directorly.app - Wrong model for your goals Proceed with MKdirs - Perfect alignment with your needs Launch this weekend - While competitors rent, you'll own Scale strategically - Build your directory empire on owned assets The choice is clear: Build equity, don't rent functionality. 🚀 Sources: Analysis based on Directorly.app official website, MKdirs.com features, and strategic business model evaluation